5 Years Analysis¶

  • 5 years analysis is slightly different with 15 years analysis，but show an identical relationship between the stock price and the unemployment rate and between the stock price and the number of license application

We observe the 5 years trend and 15 years trend are all going up¶

  • For the 15－year graph, we see a dramatically drop in price during the recession, other than that the stcok price are all going up
  • For the 5－year graph, we notice the upward sloping trend of the stock price line, while having a drop in 2015 and 2016

Regression analysis on the business license data and stock market (high, low and volume)¶

High price: there is significant relationship¶
  • P-value=0.017, t-value=-2.39, because of this small p-value and large t-value we conclude there is significnat relationship between business license application and high stock market price.
  • When the stock market price goes up, we can see the business license application goes down by 0.0117
Low price: there is significant relationship¶
    • P-value=0.011, t-value=2.552, because of this small p-value and large t-value we conclude there is significnat relationship between business license application and low stock market price.
  • When the stock market price goes up, we can see the business license application also goes up by 0.0124
Volumn: there is no significant relationship¶

Same as we see from the regression above, from this graph, we also observe there is significant relationship between business license application and low stock market price, as the regression line points to up.¶

  • We can tell there is positive relationship between business license application and low stock market price
  • As the stock market price goes low, there is more business license application

We run regression on the unemployment rate and stock market price, and found there is significant relationship¶

High stock market price: negative relationship¶
  • while holding other factors fixed, we see the p-value for the high price is 0.00, also we see the t-value is -5.133. So we conclude there is significant relationship between unemployment rate and high stock market price, because of the small P-value and large t-value
  • when the high stock market price goes up, the unemployment rate goes down by 0.0064
Low stock market price: positive relationship¶
  • while holding other factors fixed, we see the p-value for the low price is 0.00, also we see the t-value is 4.479. So we conclude there is significant relationship between unemployment rate and low stock market price, because of the small P-value and large t-value
  • when the low stock market price goes down, the unemployment rate goes up by 0.0055
